    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cheney's Way Out</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gerhard Lenski letter suggests way in which Dick Cheney could solve problem of how he, if elected, could exercise his options to buy stock in Halliburton Co without having conflict of interest</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Few Options on Cheney Option Problem'' (Business Day, Aug. 26):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Few Options on Cheney Option Problem'' (Business Day, Aug. 26):</p>
        <p>There is a fairly simple way in which Dick Cheney could solve the problem of how he, if elected, could exercise his options to buy stock in the Halliburton Company without having a conflict of interest.</p>
        <p>Few Americans, apart from tax lawyers, would object if Mr. Cheney pledged in writing that he would consider the value of the options to be what they would have been on the day before he was selected as the Republican vice-presidential nominee and that he would dedicate any profits in excess of that to reducing the national debt. He would also be entitled to take enough from the additional profits to pay any extra taxes incurred.</p>
        <p>GERHARD LENSKI  Hansville, Wash., Aug. 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
